By: Abu Sa'id ibn Abi ’l-Khayr
---
He said, ‘Even this Sûfism is polytheism (shirk).'

‘Why, O Shaykh?’ they asked.

He answered, ‘Because Sûfism consists in guarding the soul from what is
other than God; and there is nothing other than God.’
